  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Users with RepairQ Advanced and RepairQ Professional plans have the ability to switch between locations without logging out of their current location. This allows for time-saving changes while managing multiple locations.</p><p>We recommend using RepairQ in a single tab/window since changing locations only updates your current page. Any additional screens/tabs have not been updated with new information and can create issues when submitting data.</p><h3 id=\"SwitchingBetweenRepairQLocations-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1928921099/Getting+Started+Login+Password+Reset+and+User+Profile+Customization\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1928921099\" data-linked-resource-version=\"23\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Logging In/Out and Password Reset</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1928986634/Getting+Started+Clock+In+Out+of+RepairQ\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1928986634\" data-linked-resource-version=\"23\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Clocking In/Out of RepairQ</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933606938/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"SwitchingBetweenRepairQLocations-SwitchBetweenLocationsWithoutLoggingOutofRepairQ\">Switch Between Locations Without Logging Out of RepairQ</h2><p /><p>1. On the RepairQ Navigation Bar, click on the <strong>Location Dropdown</strong> and select <strong>Switch Location</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933606938/Switch%20Location%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. A Switch Location pop-up will appear. Click the dropdown to see a list of your active locations. Find the location you want to switch to and click it.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"453\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933606938/Switch%20Location%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. RepairQ will reload, and you will now be logged into the new location.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933606938/Switch%20Location%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p><p /><p /><p />",
